.TH "LIGHTNING-CHANNEL-STUCK" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-channel-stuck \- detect channels with potentially stuck HTLCs
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning channel-stuck
.RB [ --minutes
.IR N ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Reports channels that have in-flight HTLCs whose expiry timestamp
is older than
.I N
minutes ago (default 30).
Such HTLCs may indicate routing failures or unresponsive peers.
Returns an empty array if the daemon is unreachable.
.PP
Output:
.nf
[{channel_id, peer_id, stuck_htlc_count}]
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Always.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-channel-htlc-count (1),
.BR lightning-node-htlc-list (1)
